    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA model ensemble satisfies the pre-established acceptance criterion (E/uval < 1.96, percentage difference < 10%) for all three QoIs across both validation laboratories. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged and accepted on the basis that the ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration is the applicable regulatory standard and the quantitative validation metrics are satisfied within that condition. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the intended regulatory use of the FEA predictions in the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
